Use MapChat. Be social. Be visual.

== Description ==

QuickBlox MapChat is a simple plugin for WordPress, that adds a MapChat (chat integrated with map) widget to your website. You can chat over a map or in chat room.

Plugins Official Website: [http://quickblox.com/applications/mapchat/](http://quickblox.com/applications/mapchat/)

Plugin doesn't work for some reason? Use [Map Chat HTML code generator](http://quickblox.com/applications/mapchat/). It is universal and works with any website / web app. 

Cross-platform feature: [QuickBlox](http://quickblox.com/) allows your web visitors communicate with your mobile app users. If you have an iOS/Android/WP7/Blackberry app or want to build one, download MapChat code mashups from [http://quickblox.com/developers/QuickBlox_Developers](http://quickblox.com/developers/QuickBlox_Developers) put same app ID as you have in your WordPress widget and enjoy your user base united.

Any difficulties â€” check out the [5 minute guide](http://quickblox.com/developers/5_Minute_Guide) or submit your issue to our [support community](http://community.quickblox.com/quickblox/products/quickblox_wordpress_widget_mapchat).

== Installation ==

1. Upload plugin folder `quickblox-mapchat` to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory
1. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress
1. [Create QuickBlox account](https://admin.quickblox.com/register)
1. [Login to admin panel](http://admin.quickblox.com/signin)
1. Add new application ([screenshot](http://qblx.co/wqbG7x))
1. Get application parameters ([screenshot](http://qblx.co/VjuM41))
1. Go to MapChat plugin settings page and set required parameters ([screenshot](http://i.imgur.com/8wusTeo.png))
1. Place `[qbmapchat width="500px" height="500px"]` in your templates

